abstract: >
  Hymoex (Hybrid Modular Coordinated Experts) is an architectural paradigm
  for designing scalable multi-agent systems. It defines a seven-role agent
  taxonomy, three deployment modalities (One-Line MoE, One-Line Supervisor,
  MoE MultiLine), a Mixture-of-Experts gating mechanism for expert selection,
  and progressive migration functions that preserve 100% of existing agent
  definitions. Hymoex is framework-agnostic — it defines architectural
  patterns that can be applied using any execution framework (LangGraph,
  CrewAI, Pydantic AI, AutoGen, OpenAI Swarm, Vercel AI SDK, Mastra).
keywords:
